# Overview

# Table Design
CREATE TABLE hollywood (title VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY, movie_info VARCHAR, distributor VARCHAR, release_data DATE, domestic_sales INT, international_sales INT, world_sales INT, genre VARCHAR, movie_runtime VARCHAR, license VARCHAR);

# Import
This is the statement that I used to import the csv

\copy Hollywood FROM '/Users/preethinarayan/Documents/GitHub/homework06-preethi-narayan/hollywood.csv' DELIMITER ',' CSV HEADER;

I originally tried to use the COPY command, but this is the error I encountered when I did that:

hw3=# \i /Users/preethinarayan/Documents/GitHub/homework06-preethi-narayan/import_csv.sql;

psql:/Users/preethinarayan/Documents/GitHub/homework06-preethi-narayan/import_csv.sql:7: ERROR: could not open file "/Users/preethinarayan/Documents/GitHub/homework06-preethi-narayan/hollywood.csv" for reading: Permission denied

HINT: COPY FROM instructs the PostgreSQL server process to read a file. You may want a client-side facility such as psql's \copy.

I resolved this error by using the /copy command.
